	<dd><a name="comment_1714" ></a>
	<p><em><strong>thedatabase</strong> replies:</em> Healthy cynicism if you ask me Lee.  One vote in four years might have sounded like the best anyone could hope for 200 years ago, but today it seems decidedly weak.</p> <p>With luck, one day the efforts of fine sites like this one might lead to a system that is more worthwhile.  More continuous accountability than a one-in-five year circfarce is surely not too much to ask?</p> <p>Btw 'O': fines!  What a great idea... it would certainly be a start... they could start each term with a quota of perks that are successively eliminited for each transgression (ie invert the current scheme)</p>
